.] can advise you about options that will fit your particular needs. You can find more information about types of braces, including Invisalign, here.<br /><br />These options allow you to have flexibility and discretion during your treatment.\";s:27:\"flrich1571767877064_content\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"label\";s:44:\"Will orthodontic treatment fit my lifestyle?\";s:7:\"content\";s:364:\"You can do almost anything during orthodontic treatment - sing, play a musical instrument, dine out, kiss, and even have your picture taken. Some adjustments may be necessary. But, if you\'re like the vast majority of adult patients, you\'ll adjust quickly.<br /><br />New techniques and materials have made wearing braces more comfortable, and convenient than ever.\";s:27:\"flrich1571767906998_content\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"label\";s:42:\"Am I a good fit for orthodontic treatment?\";s:7:\"content\";s:295:\"During your consultation, [Dr.] can determine if you will benefit from treatment.<br /><br />After carefully analyzing the nature of your needed correction, [Dr.] will recommend the best course of treatment for improving your smile, including the different types of braces that are best for you.\";s:27:\"flrich1571767925686_content\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"label\";s:66:\"I\'m missing some teeth. Can orthodontic treatment improve my bite?\";s:7:\"content\";s:218:\"Orthodontic treatment can create or hold space to replace missing teeth.<br /><br />[Dr.] will work with your dentist or dental specialist. They will provide bridges or implants so that you can achieve the best result.\";s:27:\"flrich1571767944221_content\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"label\";s:64:\"I\'ve been treated for gum disease. Can my teeth be straightened?\";s:7:\"content\";s:289:\"[Dr.] will consult with your dentist and/or periodontist about the health of your gums.<br /><br />If you are a candidate for orthodontic treatment, you will continue regular supervision with your dentist and periodontist. In many cases, tooth alignment can improve the health of the gums.\";s:27:\"flrich1571768072399_content\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"label\";s:29:\"How much does treatment cost?\";s:7:\"content\";s:410:\"The cost of orthodontic treatment will depend on many factors, including the severity of the problem, its complexity and length of treatment. [Dr.] will be glad to discuss the cost with you before treatment begins.<br /><br />You will find that braces are more affordable today than ever. We offer a variety of convenient payment plans, and accept many dental insurance plans that include orthodontic benefits.\";s:27:\"flrich1571768091642_content\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"label\";s:63:\"Why choose an orthodontist over aligners that come in the mail?\";s:7:\"content\";s:436:\"Orthodontists are dental specialists who diagnose, prevent and treat dental and facial irregularities.<br /><br />[Dr.] received an additional three full years of specialized education beyond dental school to learn the proper way to align and straighten teeth.<br /><br />Only those with this formal education may call themselves \"orthodontists,\" and only orthodontists may be members of the American Association of Orthodontists (AAO).\";s:27:\"flrich1571768119433_content\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"collapse\";s:1:\"1\";s:10:\"open_first\";s:1:\"0\";s:10:\"label_size\";s:5:\"large\";s:12:\"item_spacing\";s:2:\"20\";s:19:\"item_spacing_medium\";s:0:\"\";s:23:\"item_spacing_responsive\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"item_border\";a:5:{s:5:\"style\";s:5:\"solid\";s:5:\"color\";s:6:\"e5e5e5\";s:5:\"width\";a:4:{s:3:\"top\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"right\";s:1:\"1\";s:6:\"bottom\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"left\";s:1:\"1\";}s:6:\"radius\";a:4:{s:8:\"top_left\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"top_right\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"bottom_left\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"bottom_right\";s:0:\"\";}s:6:\"shadow\";a:5:{s:5:\"color\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"horizontal\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"vertical\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"blur\";s: